          {
            "commit": "aa7c85da07c04d2308d7cf18f8e782eb9c0b31d3",
            "subject": "LU-13653 mdt: add EX lock protection for FLR transitions"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-06 20:59:48.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-16 01:54:14.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-13643 flr: implement immediate mirror writes for DIO",
        "message": "LU-13643 flr: implement immediate mirror writes for DIO\n\nNB: This does not implement any error handling and only works\nwith DIO\n\nImplement sequential mirror iteration for immediate mirror files\nduring Direct I/O write operations. When writing to a file with\nthe immediate mirror flag, iterate through all mirrors writing\nthe same data to each mirror sequentially.\n\nKey changes:\n- Add mirror iteration loop in cl_io_loop() for DIO writes\n- Reset iov_iter state between mirror iterations in VVP layer\n- Update LOV layer to use mirror index from iteration logic\n- Acquire/release ACTIVE_WRITER locks during immediate mirror\nwrites\n\nThis provides immediate data replication for DIO writes to\nimmediate mirror files, eliminating resync requirements.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ia96fb005f9a327fe6afd2f6a539dc7f0397ebef8\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
